               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="INS0105DD"/>
                     </origPlace> 
                     <origDate notBefore="1700" notAfter="1799" evidence="lettering" cert="medium">18th century (?)</origDate>
                     The manuscript consists of two codicological units. <ref target="#p1"/> was likely intended to serve as a guard quire. It was probably attached to <ref target="#p2"/> later, 
                     when it was resewn and/or when the manuscript found a new donor, since it has a slightly different layout and 
                     the text is written by a different scribe. The same scribe appears to have filled in the empty spaces in supplication formulas with the name of the new donors. 
                     Additionally, he rubricated divine names, names of the new donors, and some incipits in <ref target="#p2"/>.
                  </origin>
                  
                  <provenance>The name of the original donor has been erased in the supplication formulas and replaced with those of <persName ref="PRS15179WaldaAragawi">Walda ʾAragāwi</persName> and
                     <persName ref="PRS15180SawaswaDengel">Sawāswa Dǝngǝl</persName>, e.g., <locus target="#55rb #56ra"/>). 
                     On <locus target="#75ra"/> the last two letters of the original donor’s name, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማር</foreign> (mār), have been preserved.</provenance>
               </history>
                  
